channel.title: These were made in Auxy!
channel.description:
I was watching this video for the 5th or 6th time until I decided to give the soundtrack a listen since I liked it.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nwe0S4s0EAE
It doesn't say if it was made in the app, but while listening, I'm pretty sure I heard a few Auxy elements. Didn't even recognize them at first because that's just how far the app has come. Here, give it a listen yourself-
https://soundcloud.com/andrew-mcmurry-487864575/sets/pubg-vs-fortnite-soundtrack/s-W3f1H
Pretty glad the use of Auxy is extending to video production. (The video has 8 million views, too!) Got something similar to share? I'd love to hear from you.

item.title: These were made in Auxy!
item.dc:creator: TheRealJFalc
item.description:
Sorry for being a bit skeptical last night concerning these tracks. The only reason I asked was because some of Auxy’s signature sound isn’t unique to Auxy in a way. Especially the sounds developed by 7 Skies. However, I clearly see now that I was wrong xD

By the way, I actually listened to them now since, of course, it was so late at night when I saw this that I didn’t have time to. It’s definitely Auxy. Glad to see the use of Auxy in this way for certain.

item.title: These were made in Auxy!
item.dc:creator: akabillposters
item.description:
I’m pretty convinced it’s Auxy.

Too many quintessentially Auxy sounds.
Pretty convinced by time I heard the fingersnap.

The choice of sounds just seem like someone selecting from the pre-V5 Auxy.

(The bass is the only thing that isn’t immediately recognisable to me.)

 

Jelly is based from an analogue synth, so it’s likely it was something related to that.

The particular blend of tone and resonance convinces me it’s actually Jelly with a softened attack, etc…

 
Not hugely important either way.

Read full topic

item.title: These were made in Auxy!
item.dc:creator: TheRealJFalc
item.description:
El1011:

But the drum kit for sure is Auxy.

Depends on the drum kit. Since the new ones are all licensed from BlackOctopus, and they’re rather popular, they don’t only sell sound through Auxy.

akabillposters:

I dont recognize the synth used tho

Jelly (RAC Essentials), I think

Jelly is based from an analogue synth, so it’s likely it was something related to that. Although considering Jelly was specially designed for Auxy, I’d tend to agree though that it’s likely made with Auxy.

dnldrl:

I think I hear Silk (7 Skies Collection) as well

7 Skies sells presets created for both Serum, Massive and other VSTs through https://www.standalone-music.com/. It could be that one of those presets were used, but considering Jelly was specifically designed for Auxy from analogue equipment, I’d agree it is likely made using auxy, at least partially.
